.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_TeleportDisableOnHeadsetCollision
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The purpose of the Teleport Disable On Headset Collision script is to detect when the headset is colliding with a valid object and prevent teleportation from working. This is to ensure that if a user is clipping their head into a wall then they cannot teleport to an area beyond the wall.
